        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:24PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
west of Pocola, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Scullyville...                    Hackett...
Arkoma...                         Cameron...
Witcherville...                   Pocola...
Braden...                         Spiro...
Mill Creek...                     Rye Hill...
Midland...                        Moffett...
Bonanza...                        Jenson...
Cottonwood...                     Fort Smith...
Excelsior...                      Fort Smith Regional Airport...
Rock Island...                    Jenny Lind...

This includes Interstate 540 between mile markers 9 and 14.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
